fr:mainmatter.html:p:
         Remember, any set of arguments is a logic, so there's a ton of freedom here.
        You already know about the empty and universal logics.
        Here are some more examples.

the logic that contains only the two arguments p \;/\; p and p \land  q \;/\; p;

the logic that contains all and only the arguments with the conclusion p;

the logic that contains an argument \Gamma  \;/\; A if and only if A is a member of \Gamma ;

the logic that contains all and only the arguments with a finite set of premises;

the logic that contains all and only the arguments with an infinite set of premises.
